    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-26T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-26T05:00:00-05:00" n="22"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d22">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114/3065</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-26T11:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 26, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 28, 6.50 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3016. For Red Cross:</p>
                <p>Am forwarding report of Spanish inspectors dated November 1<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d22fn1">Not printed.</note> on camp at Brandenburg, containing 28
                    American prisoners of whom 19 distributed in working camps, stating that
                    treatment and discipline good but— <pb facs="0099" n="15" xml:id="pg_15"/>
                    <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>Barracks, especially regarding heating, lighting and exposure to rain,
                            unsatisfactory;</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>That petty officers Kline and Roop compelled to work;</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>Dr. <persName>John W. Brown</persName>, medical officer of <hi
                                rend="italic">Esmeraldas</hi>, detained contrary to Geneva
                            convention.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Spanish Embassy has taken up these three points with Foreign Office. Food served
                    unsatisfactory but prisoners are receiving packages regularly and appear not
                    suffering in health or otherwise. Inspectors not allowed to converse without
                    witness. I suggest that you secure, if possible, confirmation of Doctor Brown’s
                    medical status. <persName corresp="#p_DEL1">Dresel</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
